LAGOS – Lagos State has stood still at the ongoing programme of the formal declaration for the Peoples Democratic Party  (PDP) by the Lagos4Lagos, convener, Olajide Adediran, popularly called Jandor who is saying bye bye to the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) in Lagos State as he moves into the main opposition party with a mammoth crowd of supporters. It is happening now in Tafawa Balewa Square (TBS) Lagos, where Chief Bode George, former deputy national chairman of the PDP, Dele Momodu, a presidential hopeful, Honourable Rita Orji, Dr Bimbo Ogunkelu, Mrs Aduke Maina, Mrs. Kofo Bucknor- Akelere, Chief Kuye and other prominent chieftains of the party already on ground, while the national chairman, state governors and other dignitaries are being awaited. The crownd at the event has shown that the main oposition party in Lagos State has meant every word when it said that it will take over the state in 2023. 2023: PDP Set To Take Over Lagos As Ayu, Saraki, Wike, Makinde,… I’m Not Seeking To Be President, I Want To Be APC Chairman… Details shortly.